Pre-Game Insights: Hungary have gradually improved in class and are now rightfully considered a strong team.
They secured a spot in Nations League Division A and not only remained there but almost won their elite-level group in the last cycle.
They also confidently qualified for the Euros, winning their group with 18 points from 8 matches—4 points ahead of Serbia.
Bosnia disappointed in the last cycle, qualifying for only one major tournament in their history.
In the 2023 qualifiers, Bosnia earned just 9 points from 10 matches and finished second-to-last.
Bosnia started the Nations League against the Netherlands away, where they suffered a defeat more fitting for a hockey game—2-5.
